<font color="#FF0000">THE WALL</font><br>
<tt>Sun Dec 15 16:38:43 US/Eastern 1996
</tt><p>
<br>
I spent two years in Vietnam with a combat unit and as an advisor to the Vietnamese. I have never been to the &quot;wall&quot;, although I live fairly close to Washington. I will never go there. It is a tombstone around which troubled souls gather for various reasons. There is a place for tombstones, but not in the middle of the nation's capitol.  It is too depressing. I believe that monuments should honor the dead - those that gave that last great measure of devotion and sacrifice for their country. I do not want to hear from any of you.
<p><code>--   (WG) </code><p>


